dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Volos, sheet G-8.A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4410)
dc_description_s: AMS. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4410. Alternate title: Volos, Greece.Transverse Mercator projection. Principal meridians are Athens and Greenwich. Universal transverse Mercator grid. UTM grid added, gradient tints deleted by AMS, 1948. Principal meridians are Athens and Greenwich. UTM grid values revised, 1951. Relief shown by 100 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a Greek glossary. Compiled by 512 Fd. Survey Coy., R.E., Sept., 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1951.
